author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Cook the rice: Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #medium pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Once boiling, add the @brown rice{3/4%cup} and cook for ~{25-30%minutes}, until tender. Drain, (just like pasta) and return to the #pot. Keep covered until the rest of the meal is ready.

Peel the @carrots{1%piece} with a #peeler{} and shave it into ribbons lengthwise. Repeat with the @zucchini{1%piece}. Trim the ends of the @scallions{2%unit}, then thinly slice. Cut the @baby broccoli{6%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Thinly slice the @button mushrooms{8%ounce}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%clove}. Peel and mince the @ginger{1%thumb}.

Toss the scallions in a #small bowl{} with the @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{}.

Make the ginger-soy sauce: In another small bowl, combine the @soy sauce{1%jar}, garlic, ginger, and @sugar{1%tsp}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the carrots and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, tossing for ~{4-5%minutes}, until crisp-tender. Remove from the pan and set aside. Repeat with the zucchini. Remove from the pan and set aside. Add the broccolini and mushrooms and a drizzle of oil to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{6-8%minutes}, until golden brown and slightly crispy. Season with salt and pepper and set aside with the other veggies. Optional: If you've got them, this would be the time to fry up two @?eggs{2} sunny-side up in the pan!

If not, proceed to step 6.

Pour the ginger-soy sauce into the pan, reserving a spoonful. Simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}, until thickened.

Plate and serve: Plate the rice and arrange the zucchini, carrots, broccolini, and mushrooms on top. Sprinkle with pickled scallions and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Top with the sunny-side eggs, if using. Drizzle with the reserved ginger-soy sauce and @hot sauce{3%teaspoon} (to taste). Enjoy!